
Overview of noun enlightenment

The noun enlightenment has 3 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                  
1. (1) enlightenment -- (education that results in understanding and the spread of knowledge)
2. nirvana, enlightenment -- ((Hinduism and Buddhism) the beatitude that transcends the cycle of reincarnation; characterized by the extinction of desire and suffering and individual consciousness)
3. Enlightenment, Age of Reason -- (a movement in Europe from about 1650 until 1800 that advocated the use of reason and individualism instead of tradition and established doctrine; "the Enlightenment brought about many humanitarian reforms")
